Defending Champion Vettel Edges Hamilton for Malaysian Grand Prix Pole

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-04-09T12:00:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-09/defending-champion-vettel-edges-hamilton-for-malaysian-grand-prix-pole.html
Defending Formula One world champion
Sebastian Vettel edged  Lewis Hamilton  to claim pole position for
tomorrow’s Malaysian Grand Prix.  Red Bull’s Vettel had the fastest time of 1 minute, 34.870
seconds to beat McLaren’s Hamilton by 0.104 seconds in today’s
qualifying in Sepang. It’s the second consecutive pole for the
German, who won the season-opening race in  Australia  two weeks
ago.  “It was very close in the end with the McLaren guys, so
I’m happy to get the pole,” Vettel said in comments on Formula
One’s web site. “Big compliments to the guys in the team.”  Red Bull’s  Mark Webber  qualified third ahead of McLaren’s
 Jenson Button , Ferrari’s  Fernando Alonso  and Renault’s Nick
Heidfeld. Ferrari’s  Felipe Massa , Renault’s Vitaly Petrov,  Nico
Rosberg  of Mercedes and Sauber’s Kamui Kobayashi rounded out the
top ten qualifiers.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  